      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2011 BMW M3 (E92) Coupe, preserved in absolute showroom condition. This specimen features the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8, delivering linear power delivery to an 8,400 RPM redline through a tactile 6-speed longitudinal manual transmission. Mechanically flawless, the vehicle has undergone proactive preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement with VAC coated bearings and updated throttle body actuators. The chassis remains rigid and corrosion-free, equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and a Variable M Differential Lock for precise lateral dynamics. The Alpine White paint retains its factory depth with no discernible swirling, while the Novillo leather interior shows zero bolster wear. No modifications, no track time, and a documented service history that validates its pristine mechanical state.",
